{
  "texts": [
    "-Self-verification.",
    "As an extension of explainability, LLMs verify the accuracy of their own output using, for instance, fact-checking tools or other methods to ensure that the text generated by the LLM is consistent with its knowledge base.",
    "LLMs can also self-verify by critically analyzing its own output (Dhuliawala et al., 2023).",
    "Mitigation is greatly helped by the availability of metrics that quantify hallucinations.",
    "TruthfulQA is a benchmark dataset that comprises 817 questions across various domains such as health and politics (Lin et al., 2022)."
  ]
}